TextBody:
Hi Julian,

Thanks for reaching out!
We have a tool for Windows and a script for MacOS machines that can uninstall the clients, please let me know which one you need.

Before we can send over the mentioned tool, we need your written confirmation that the tool will only be used by one of the administrators, safely removed from the user's machine once it is not needed anymore and that the tool will not be shared with any third parties.

Best regards,
Botond Biro | Technical Support Engineer

Julian

Hi again Botond,

Thank you very much for the link!  I have a question about the uninstall tool.  Let's say I had USB and other Device blocking turned on so the client is preventing the usage of the device/drive.  When I use the uninstall tool will it automatically stop the blocking of the device, or will it leave it in a permanently blocked situation?

Thank you again,
Julian
Subject: Netwrix Support Ticket #414308 - Uninstall Script on Windows Endpoint

TextBody:
Hi Julian,

If the blocking is done by EPP, after uninstalling, the USB drives will be allowed.
But if the blocking is done by other software, I can't say if they will be allowed after uninstalling the EPP agent.

Best regards,
